pchangeofhands.pchangeofhand:
The handwriting seems to have be executed by a trained, but very uncertain hand. It is characterized by slightly right-sloping letters, rounded and curved letter shapes (e.g., ሰ በ ወ). A few letters appear more angular (e.g., መ ዐ). 
Some distinctive features:
- ጵ has the 6th order marker set up on the vertical stroke at the top, oriented to the left (e.g., fols. 26va l.23, 83rb l.11);
- ሎ has the 7th order marker at the top, not in the middle (e.g., fol. 102ra l.3); a few times it appears attached directly at the body of the letter, without horizontal stroke (fol. 103vb);
- the tops of መ ሠ ወ are slanted to the left; 
- መ and ሙ have the right loop detached from the ruled line; 
- ፲ appears occasionally in the form with a ring (fol. 42vb l.10);
- ፬ tends to triangular shape, downwards oriented;
- ፮ is with the loop open, looking like “compressed” ፯ (e.g., fol. 114rb).

ppunctuations.ppunctuation:
Executed: not quite regularly;
Usage: not always logical.
Dividers:
I.Colon.
II. Colon with dashes above and below (esp. fol. 79ra, l.17);
red and black dot vertical colon with dashes above and below (esp. fols.: 27rb, l.9; 30va, l.2; 124rb, l.13; 137rb, l.6);
four dot asterisk (e.g. fols.: 14ra, ls. 9, 12; 21vb, l.1; 27rb, ls. 1, 4, 6; 36ra, l.3); 
nine dot asterisk (used throughout the text). 
Sentence dividers are accompanied by the paragraph signs, on the left from the text column and between the two columns (used throughout the Ms.). 
III. Doubled nine dot asterisks, with lines in between (esp. fols.: 29ra, l.2; 29vb, l.24; 46va, ls.10,18; 68rb, ls. 1, 2); 
nine dot asterisks, connected with lines (esp. fols.: 52vb, l.6; 61vb, l.31; 94rb, l.16); 
four dot asterisks, connected with lines (esp. fols.: 73va, l.8; 80vb, l.14);
chain of black and red dots (e.g. fols.:  1va, l.28; 29ra, l.2; 19vb, l.24; 31rb, l.17; 68rb, l.1; 80vb, ls. 8, 11; 100vb, l.9; 182vb, l.9);
chain of black lines and red and black dots (esp. fols.: 13rb, l.2; 16rb, l.9; 18va, ls. 18, 23, 28; 27ra, ls. 27-28; 46va, l.19; 55vb, ls. 15, 16; 144va, l.1; 175va, l.21; 178rb, l.20; 182ra, l.11; 182vb, l.18); 
chains of black and red lines, followed by a chain of small crux ansata signs (esp. fol. 46va);
coronis (esp. fols.: 131r, 142r, 144va).
Crux ansata with coronis, marking the beginning of each new text (esp. fols.: 46va, 112va, 148va, 150va, 175va).
